NAME		3channel
SYNTAX		3channel <channel> <message>
		3channel <channel> :<message>
		3channel <channel> @<host>
DESCRIPTION	Broadcast a message on an intermud-III channel.
		With the leading : character, the message will be an emote.
		This command is not often used directly but rather via a
		global alias. (See list of global aliases as distributed).

		The third form of the command sends a request for the
		listeners to the remote host.
